jalse.entities.functions

Class StreamEntitiesFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • jalse.entities.functions.StreamEntitiesFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntityMethodFunction, java.util.function.Function<java.lang.reflect.Method,EntityMethod>

    public class StreamEntitiesFunction
extends java.lang.Object
implements EntityMethodFunction
    This is a method function for StreamEntities annotation. It will resolve an StreamEntitiesMethod to be used by the entity typing system. This differs from the usual streaming of Entity as it also lets you stream a subset of Entity using EntityID (so adding to any method will cause it to filter).

    The next example signature will resolve to EntityContainer.streamEntities(). 
     
  @StreamEntities
  Stream<Entity> streamGhosts();
    The next example signature will resolve to EntityContainer.streamEntitiesOfType(Class). 
     
  @StreamEntities
  Stream<Ghost> streamGhosts();
    The next example signature will resolve to EntityContainer.streamEntitiesAsType(Class). 
     
  @StreamEntities(ofType = false)
  Stream<Ghost> streamGhosts();
    The next example signature will show how to use one of the above examples with a subset. 
     
  @EntityID(mostSigBits = 0, leastSigBits = 1)
  @EntityID(mostSigBits = 0, leastSigBits = 2)
  @EntityID(mostSigBits = 0, leastSigBits = 3)
  @EntityID(mostSigBits = 0, leastSigBits = 4)
  @EntityID(mostSigBits = 0, leastSigBits = 5)
  @StreamEntities
  Stream<Ghost> streamGhosts();
    NOTE: This function will throw exceptions if StreamEntities is present but the method signature is invalid.
    See Also:
    DefaultEntityProxyFactory
